      "writtenOn": "2021-06-29T21:57:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\"typed nil\" (https://golang.org/doc/faq#nil_error) is a common problem and go it is usually solved in a place that produces interface-typed values rather than consumes them: i.e. change your test to pass `nil` instead of a typed-nil.\n\nOtherwise such checks would need to be added *everywhere*.",
